# 4. Structural Diagrams & Schematics

## 4.1 UML Class Diagram — Composite Pattern

```mermaid
classDiagram
    class Component {
        <<interface>>
        +operation() void
        +add(Component c) void
        +remove(Component c) void
        +getChild(int i) Component
    }
    class Leaf {
        +operation() void
    }
    class Composite {
        -children: List~Component~
        +operation() void
        +add(Component c) void
        +remove(Component c) void
        +getChild(int i) Component
    }
    class Client {
        +execute(Component c) void
    }

    Component <|.. Leaf
    Component <|.. Composite
    Composite o-- Component : children
    Client --> Component
```

> [!NOTE]
> **Diagram Interpretation:**
> - The **hollow triangle arrow** `<|..` denotes *realization* (implements/extends).
> - The **diamond arrow** `o--` denotes *aggregation* (Composite has-a list of Components).
> - The **plain arrow** `-->` denotes *dependency* (Client uses Component).

## 4.2 Object Tree — Recursive Composition

```mermaid
graph TD
    rootComposite[Composite Root] --> childComp1[Composite Child A]
    rootComposite --> leaf1[Leaf Node 1]
    rootComposite --> leaf2[Leaf Node 2]
    childComp1 --> leafA1[Leaf Node A1]
    childComp1 --> leafA2[Leaf Node A2]

    rootComposite:::composite
    childComp1:::composite
    leaf1:::leaf
    leaf2:::leaf
    leafA1:::leaf
    leafA2:::leaf

    classDef composite fill:#FFD700,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px,color:#000
    classDef leaf fill:#90EE90,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px,color:#000
```

## 4.3 Sequence Diagram — Client-Composite Interaction

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant Client
    participant Comp as Composite
    participant Leaf1 as Leaf A
    participant Leaf2 as Leaf B
    participant SubComp as Sub-Composite

    Client->>Comp: operation()
    Comp->>Comp: own logic
    Comp->>Leaf1: operation()
    Leaf1-->>Comp: result
    Comp->>Leaf2: operation()
    Leaf2-->>Comp: result
    Comp->>SubComp: operation()
    SubComp->>SubComp: own logic + recursion
    SubComp-->>Comp: aggregated result
    Comp-->>Client: final result
```

## 4.4 Block-Level Functional Architecture

```mermaid
flowchart LR
    A[Client Code] --> B{Component Reference}
    B -->|actual type = Leaf| C[Leaf operation EXECUTES]
    B -->|actual type = Composite| D[Composite operation EXECUTES]
    D --> E[Loop over children]
    E --> F{Each child type}
    F -->|Leaf| C
    F -->|Composite| D
    C --> G[Return result to caller]
    D --> G
```

<!-- SECTION_4_END -->

